    <title>
        Ressources
    </title>
    
    <para>
        Different resources are using in these tutorials. You will find common information in this chapter.
    </para>

    <section>
        <title>
            Sources
        </title>

        <para>
            A collection of source code examples are available in Geotoolkit official project
        </para>
        <para>
            Online :
            <link xlink:href="http://hg.geotoolkit.org/geotoolkit-pending/file/0237bc78daa2/demos">
                <acronym>GeotoolKit Mercurial repository</acronym>
            </link>
        </para>

        <section>
            <title>
                Get and update sources
            </title>

            <para>
                The distributed revision control system used with GeotoolKit is  
                <link xlink:href="http://mercurial.selenic.com/">
                    <acronym>Mercurial</acronym>
                </link>.
            </para>

            <para>
                When Mercurial installed, you can copy sources with the command :
            </para>

            <programlisting>
                hg clone http://hg.geotoolkit.org/geotoolkit-pending geotk-pending
            </programlisting>

            <para>
                To get the last version (update) :
            </para>
            <programlisting>
                hg pull -u
            </programlisting>

        </section>

    </section>

    <section>
        <title>
            Precompile
        </title>

        <para>
            All projects compile every nights and archives are public.
        </para>

        <para>
            <link xlink:href="http://jenkins.geomatys.com/">
                <acronym>Jenkins repository</acronym>
            </link>
        </para>
    </section>

    <section>
        <title>
            Local compilation
        </title>

        <para>
            Compilation requiered :
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <link xlink:href="http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html">
                            <acronym>JDK 1.6+</acronym>
                        </link>
                        with extensions
                        <link xlink:href="http://java.net/projects/jai/">
                            <acronym>JAI</acronym>
                        </link>
                        (pre-installed on Mac) and
                        <link xlink:href="http://java.net/projects/jai-imageio/">
                            <acronym>ImageIO</acronym>
                        </link>
                    </para>
                </listitem>

                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <link xlink:href="http://maven.apache.org/">
                            <acronym>Maven 3.0.4 or more</acronym>
                        </link>
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </para>

        <para> When you have installed these, use this command to compile :
        </para>
        <programlisting>
            mvn clean install -DskipTests
        </programlisting>
        <para>
            Compile time depends of your hardware and your Internet connection. The first compilation is longer to get differents packages missing (around thirty minutes the first time).
        </para>
        <para>
            GeotoolKit Jars are in the subdirectory 
            <emphasis>target</emphasis>.
        </para>
    </section>
</chapter>